manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Munchkin Arm & Hammer Stay Fresh Nursery Deodorizers From baby’s room to the bathroom, household odors can really sneak up on you. Now there’s a simple way to help rid your home of offensive smells. These small deodorizing discs are powered by the natural odor-absorbing strength of Arm & Hammer baking soda and act as portable air fresheners. They’re great for diaper bags, hampers, changing tables and more. Even non baby-specific areas like shoe closets and garbage cans can benefit from these small but mighty odor neutralizers.

The stink ends here. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for Small Closets
reviews.reviewText: We have a small linen closet that also has a dirty clothes hamper in it. So, I was looking for something to get rid of the odor. Pro or con - depending on your preference - they have a slight scent when you open the package, but you don't smell the scent after that....like when you open the closet door (which I prefer). Pro - they work great at eliminating odor. They may be mini size, but they are mighty! I have found that other scented brands can have an over-powering smell that overwhelms me when I open the door, and doesn't do as good a job at eliminating the odor. Con - there is no adhesive for sticking. Although you could probably use command strips or something like to hang. My work around was to place two in my closet - one on the edge of the top shelf, and one on the edge of the bottom shelf, where they won't get bumped or moved. I think these would work well in larger closets too, you would just need to use more depending on the closet size, and make sure you space them out for maximum coverage. I don't know yet if it will last the full 90 days, I'm hoping to get at least 30 days. So far, I think this is a great find, and it's doing what I need it to do. I would recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Nice idea, not amazing results
reviews.reviewText: I wasn't expecting too much from these, but they're not great for getting rid of diaper odor. I did put one in the bathroom trashcan and it seems to help in there with the occasional diaper, but it doesn't hold up against the nursery diaper bin.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but effective
reviews.reviewText: I was a little hesitant to get these because of other reviews that the scent isn’t strong. However, I was pleasantly surprised at how well they block the odor in the diaper genie. I have it stuck in the top where the slot is for the brand charcoal filters and it has drastically reduced the bad smell that can permeate when it’s opened. I’m pretty sensitive to perfumes and I don’t smell whatever the scent in these is supposed to be. As long as I’m not smelling the poo diapers then that’s all I care about.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Wrong size for the pucking diaper pails...
reviews.reviewText: When looking for the Arm& Hammer deodorant puck replacements for the Munchkin Step Diaper Pail, these are the first things that come up. The image looks EXACTLY like the Arm& Hammer deodorant pucks that came with the Munchkin Step Diaper Pail. The description states "Great for diaper bags, diaper pails,... " Unfortunately, the parenthetic warning "(not for use as a replacement in the lid of Munchkin Diaper Pails)" is buried at the end of the same bullet touting that these are appropriate and "Great" for diaper pails—with the text split between two lines, and the word "not" on a separate line from "for." Nothing mentions that they make a miniature version that looks the same in photos as the one that fits the item that you named in the search bar. The measurements are almost unnoticeable. The numbers "1.97 x 1.97 x 0.79 inches" are down the page, next to Product Dimensions—adjacent to the item's Best Sellers Rank of "#1 in Diaper Pail Deodorizers." Again, here's the problem: THEY'RE THE WRONG SIZE! THEY'RE TINY! THEY DON'T FIT THE MUNCHKIN STEP DIAPER PAIL! And the warning is hidden in the listing. If you're the type of consumer that has the time and focus to carefully comb through an Amazon page looking for a product's carefully hidden booby-traps, then you might catch this. But if you're the type of consumer that's likely to shop for diaper pail related products—that is, a frazzled parent raising an infant during a pandemic, short on sleep and with a reduced attention span—then there's a good chance that you might miss this buried lead. C'MON AMAZON! This has been called to your attention before, by approximately 10% of the reviews. Your well-disguised, carefully-hidden language, written by lawyers for the purpose of maintaining deniability, isn't working for a significant number of customers. Fix this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023

reviews.reviewText: Bought these to use in some cabinets. As far as odor elimination, they work well. However, I did not realize they were going to smell like baby powder. A little odd when opening up a kitchen cabinet LOL.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: For 1.5 years I have been using the diaper bin without anything to stop the smell. I never put very dirty diapers in, just wees, but still, the smell is pretty bad when you open the lid. I put one of these in and it worked so well, there is literally NO smell. Highly recommend!
